The paper presents a method for environment-driven variation of the length of the spatiotemporal window for localization algorithms, which is a topic related to robotics (cs.RO) and computer vision (cs.CV). The method involves searching for the most significant localization hypothesis, which can be seen as a machine learning problem, thus making it relevant to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper also discusses the evaluation of the proposed method on benchmark datasets, which is related to systems and control (cs.SY).
